 Job Description 
Your Role 
The intern will help monitor our current operations and determine more efficient processes. The Business Excellence Co-Op/Intern‚Äôs responsibilities include participating in project pipeline discussions; analyzing current state of business operations through VOC surveys, data analysis/mining, process mapping, etc; assisting in improving staff workflows to reduce waste and inefficiencies that ultimately improve the customer experience. Current projects include but are not limited to: reducing duplication in master data, simplifying the returns/exchanges process, reducing backorders and improving backorder communication, and simplifying to scale customer discount structures. 
The Business Excellence Co-Op/Intern will be expected to go through several internal lean six sigma trainings and apply the classroom learnings to practical environments. 
 
 Your Responsibilities 
Support lean initiatives, including assisting in planning, performing, and sustainment of Kaizen events 
Improve back office processes to maximize efficiency and reduce waste 
Develop and implement process and methods improvements 
Develop and maintain process documentation such as standard work and control plans 
Participate in special projects supporting the business as required, potentially including artificial intelligence and machine learning 
 
 Qualifications 
 
Working toward a degree in industrial engineering, math, statistics, or a related field 
Must have the ability to understand and apply lean concepts, data analysis, and project management principles to drive process and project efficiency 
Must have the ability to perform at a high level in a fast-paced environment while managing multiple projects at once 
Excellent critical thinking and problem-solving skills 
Must be a self-starter that can perform well without constant supervision 
Ability to communicate and present clearly and effectively 
Troubleshooting skills and attention to detail 
Documentation and organizational skills 
Proficiency in MS Office 
Must have transportation to and from internship 
